        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:09PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 209 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over George Washington
Carver St Pk, or 8 miles east of Cartersville, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Canton, Cartersville, Woodstock, Holly Springs, Emerson, Kellogg
Creek, Red Top Mountain State Park, Oak Grove, Little River Landing,
George Washington Carver St Pk, Lebanon, Sutallee, Hobgood Park, and
Bridgemill.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
